my configuration file for example is:

    font pango:DejaVu 11
It requires ttf-dejavu of course ;)

But this will only set's a font for window headings and i3bar

If you are searching for a fancy looking window manager you should look out for something else. Maby Ubuntu.</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Oct 2014 22:36:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4695/fonts-look-strange/?answer=4696#post-id-4696</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Michael for &lt;p&gt;Why does i3 itself and the terminal (terminator) look so strange and is there a way to fix it?&lt;/p&gt;

